Kubernetes Ingress-controller

exp - why the ingress controller comes into 

optional - kubeproxy will assign an ip address to static ip adress to service component.

ntk - if we allocate nodeport as service mode to pods then the port allocation range would by default port allocation range starts from 30000 - 32000

1)load-balancer type service - 


practically implement ingress resource onto kubernetes cluster

prerequiste to it
1) ingress-controller has to be installed on in k cluster
to ingress controller install via helm charts
2)ingress resource - set of rules

helm repo add ingress-nginx https://kubernetes.github.io/ingress-nginx
				# helm repo update
				# helm install ingress-nginx ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx --namespace ingress-nginx --create-namespace
using above 3 commands we can install ingress-controller onto kubernetes cluster

after installing it can check with commands like
kubectl get ingress-controller

